<p>i am trying to draw in canvas with transforming the div size but i am not able to draw exactly from mouse point, there is some distance between mouse and line where is actual drawing happen.</p>  <p><strong>CSS</strong></p>  <pre><code>canvas {     border: 1px solid #ccc;     transform: scale(0.5) } </code></pre>  <p><strong>JS</strong></p>  <pre><code>var el = document.getElementById('c'); var ctx = el.getContext('2d'); var isDrawing;  el.onmousedown = function (e) {     isDrawing = true;     ctx.moveTo(e.clientX, e.clientY); }; el.onmousemove = function (e) {     if (isDrawing) {         ctx.lineTo(e.clientX, e.clientY);         ctx.stroke();     } };  el.onmouseup = function () {     isDrawing = false; }; </code></pre>  <p><strong>HTML</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;canvas id="c" width="500" height="300"&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt; </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/vishalvarshney/Lqbeqjzb/" rel="nofollow">Demo fiddle</a></p>